        "text": "*[Bug 17684] X11 event handling regression (?) in scrolling detection*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=17684>\n\n--- Comment #6 from Trevor Davis (<mailto:trevor.l.davis@gmail.com|trevor.l.davis@gmail.com>) ---\nCreated attachment 3709\n  --&gt; <https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/attachment.cgi?id=3709&amp;action=edit>\nAlso add scroll detection to `windows()`\n\nThis patch augments the previous patch by also adding scroll detection to\n`windows()` using the same `X11()` style system where a scroll up is\nrepresented by a mouse down and mouse up event with integer `3L` and a scroll\ndown is represented by a mouse down and mouse up event with integer `4L`.\n\nI've also tweaked the testing code from a previous comment to also provide\ninformation about mouse x\/y coordinates to help verify that the patched code\npreserves (x,y) mouse coordinate conventions when the various events are\ntriggered:\n\n```\nmousemove &lt;- function(buttons, x, y) {\n    cat(sprintf(\"mousemove   buttons=%s x=%.3f y=%.3f\\n\", toString(buttons), x,\ny))\n    NULL\n}\nmousedown &lt;- function(buttons, x, y) {\n    cat(sprintf(\"mousedown   buttons=%s x=%.3f y=%.3f\\n\", toString(buttons), x,\ny))\n    NULL\n}\nmouseup &lt;- function(buttons, x, y) {\n    cat(sprintf(\"mouseup     buttons=%s x=%.3f y=%.3f\\n\", toString(buttons), x,\ny))\n    NULL\n}\nkeystroke &lt;- function(key) {\n    cat(sprintf(\"keystroke   key=%s\\n\", key))\n    NULL\n}\n\nif (identical(.Platform$OS.type, \"unix\")) {\n    x11(type = \"Xlib\")\n} else {\n    windows()\n}\npar(mar = c(0, 0, 0, 0))\nplot.new()\ngetGraphicsEvent(onMouseMove = mousemove, onMouseDown = mousedown,\n                 onMouseUp = mouseup, onKeybd = keystroke)\n```\n\nNote unlike with `X11` where scrolling are modeled as discrete button presses\nthat instead Windows scrolling events also have information about scrolling\ndeltas.  Currently the magnitudes of these scrolling deltas are being ignored\nsince `doMouseEvent` currently does not have the signature to support passing\nsuch scroll delta information.\n\nOne side effect of this patch is that in `windows()` scrolling should now\nterminate `locator()` which will match the current `x11()` behavior.  For\n`locator()` what should happen for `windows()` isn't documented but for `X11()`\nit says:\n\n&gt; For the usual 'X11' device the identification process is terminated by pressing any mouse button other than the first.",
