        "text": "*[Bug 19078] New: Add flexiblas detection to autoconf scripts*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19078>\n\n            Bug ID: 19078\n           Summary: Add flexiblas detection to autoconf scripts\n           Product: R\n           Version: R-devel (trunk)\n          Hardware: All\n                OS: Linux\n            Status: UNCONFIRMED\n          Severity: enhancement\n          Priority: P5\n         Component: Wishlist\n          Assignee: <mailto:R-core@R-project.org|R-core@R-project.org>\n          Reporter: <mailto:andrew@robbinsa.me|andrew@robbinsa.me>\n\nCreated attachment 3711\n  --&gt; <https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/attachment.cgi?id=3711&amp;action=edit>\npatch\n\nFlexiblas is the default implementation of blas for all redhat-like distros\nsince fedora 33 and rhel9. Currently those distros specify\n--with-blas=flexiblas explicitly, which does work, but should not be necessary.\nAutoconf-Archives has had the ability to detect it automatically for the last\nfew years--I have simply ported that over to R.m4.\n\n(I also was the author of this PR to autoconf-archives, so there's no\nattribution issues here)",
